Author: Ericky Dos Santos <ericky@playtron.one>
Date:   Sat Feb 28 03:44:45 2026 +0000

    freedreno: force linear tiling for R8 (cpp=1) textures on a7xx_gen3+
    
        A7XX gen3+ / A8XX GPUs have a hardware bug where tiled R8 (cpp=1)
        textures produce corruption when partial sub-region updates are
        performed via buffer-to-image copies. This manifests as horizontal
        line artifacts at tile boundaries (e.g. every 4 pixels for R8_UNORM
        with 16x4 tile size).
    
        The issue is specific to the tiled layout for cpp=1 images, which use
        different alignment parameters (pitchalign=1, heightalign=32) compared
        to wider formats. Neither disabling UBWC (TU_DEBUG=noubwc) nor
        flushing all caches (TU_DEBUG=flushall) resolves the corruption,
        confirming it is a tiling layout issue rather than a cache coherency
        problem.
    
        Add an r8_tiling_quirk device property set on a7xx_gen3 (inherited by
        all A8XX variants) and force linear tile mode for affected images in
        tu_image.cc.

